### Overall Observations

- Very friendly and accommodating aid, crew, and spectators  
- Relatively hot weather for 2026, projected high was 68 during race period  
  - Tokyo 2026 will likely be cooler but still warm  
- Very Japanese field of competitors  
  - Tokyo will likely be more international  
- Time cutoffs are likely not an issue if you show up on time and run at a pace faster than 5:00:00

### General Notes

- Fewer bathroom stations than American marathons (e.g. Chicago)  
  - Open/doorless urinal bathroom stations  
- Tokyo public transportation is world-class, but you do have to walk to it, walk during it, and walk after  
  - This means that after your marathon is over, you will have to walk back to the subway station if that is your plan  
- Calling out â€œsumimasenâ€ (sorry/excuse me) in advance seems to work if you are trying to pass someone in front of you  
- Bring coins with you in case you want something out of the many drink vending machines \- a spectator might be willing to get it for you
